- Collect carrier force gauge data for all chambers (Toh KC)
- Change P18, 19 & P20 double air vent valve. (Toh KC)
- Check P20 & 22 back latch at behind chamber coupling side. (Toh KC)
- Change P8 & P9 , P19 & P20 GV Cover secure block to modify type. (Toh KC)
- Change P20 Drypump
> Check all bias springs' condition contact alignment.
> Start all turbopumps.
> Check all cryopumps' compressors' helium level.
> Top up CRC 3 & 6
> Install all GVs and GV covers
> Mount all targets, youtec guns and shield parts.
> Check all chambers' rail alignment by using 0.1mm york carrier.
> Check all chambers' shield parts' particles by using UV torch
> Insert 1.5mm carrier to check scratches.
> Insert all new carriers and pump down all chambers.
> Perform internal leak check.OK
> Perform external  leak check.OK
> Autorun and test fire.
> Check all TDU vibration.
> Heat run with toulene air-exhuast for 300s.
> Monitor alignment. OK
> Handover to Production
